body.description: Teething babies gnaw on everything they can get their hands on -- including their beloved pacifiers. That's why Munchkin created a multitasking soother that's easy on baby's gums, in pastels that are easy on the eyes. The silly-soothe & teethe silicone pacifier & teether set includes two durable, multi-textured pacifiers that soothe sore gums with their uniquely ridged surface. Made from 100% food grade silicone in aesthetically pleasing tones, the one-piece design is safe for even the tiniest teethers to chew. productInformation.name: Care instructions
productInformation.value: ‎To Clean: Before first use, place pacifier in boiling water for 5 minutes or steam sterilize, allow to cool, and squeeze out any trapped water. Wash and inspect before use. Hand wash in warm, soapy water. Top-rack dishwasher safe. Air-dry.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: A pacifier and teether in one! Teething babies gnaw on everything they can get their hands on — including their beloved pacifiers. That's why Munchkin created a multitasking soother that's easy on baby's gums, in pastels that are easy on the eyes. Made from 100% food grade silicone in aesthetically pleasing tones, the one-piece design is safe for even the tiniest teethers to chew. The pacifiers' ability to pull double duty means less clutter and longer usefulness, too — making it a smart and practical addition to your nursery essentials list.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These are amazing for newborns! You’re supposed to switch from these when they get older because these types of soothe pacis can mess their teeth but they are great for them to chew on when they are teething!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awsome ! Amazing! Buy them!!!
reviews.reviewText: We love these!!!! Buy them its 100% worth it might as well buy 2 packages though because your baby will love these. We found these when my daughter was about 10 months old she had 2 button Muller's and a top tooth coming in she was mirabel until we got these 2 of 3 teeth popped threw with in 48 hours and the third about 72 hours it relaxed her and helped her teeth also teething in the middle of the night she quit waking up crying chewing on her fingers she now peacefully sleeps thanks to these wounder binkies

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I bit better than the Razbaby Razberry, in my opinion.
reviews.reviewText: My daughter likes it more than the Razberry by Razbaby (I really think its just a texture thing.) It's pretty durable. (so far) My only complaint is everything sticks to it! Other than that she's happy with it so, so am I.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Teething baby loves this
reviews.reviewText: I got a sample of this teether in a baby registry sample box. My son has loved it since he started teething. I recently lost it and was so thankful that this duo set was available for purchase. My son is not a fan of the binky, but I think this does it for him as far as chewing and him being able to maneuver it for side chewing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not For Older Kids
reviews.reviewText: I bought these because they were recommended for young ones with teeth. My kiddo had no interest in using these whatsoever. He is 4 with oral sensory issues but has never rejected a pacifier before. I think it is too small—definitely for younger kids and not toddlers with teeth.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 28, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice shape and design
reviews.reviewText: I like this teether because it has texture on every side and is just like the dr Brown pacifier and bottle nipple except it has ridges so there’s a better chance of it being accepted. Cute too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for our doggos!
reviews.reviewText: Held up extremely well under the conditions we are using them. Using with toothpaste enzymes for oral hygeine with two older dogs. Also covering nipple portion with peanut butter and freezing them, to be offered as a special treat. No damage to the pacifiers after months of use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not a fan
reviews.reviewText: I brought these because my baby is teething and she was constantly chewing on her pacifier. I was excited to see if she like them. My baby is not picking when it comes to pacifiers she will suck on any brand any shape. She did not like these at all. It was a complete waste of money. I can't even return these because I already opened the pack.
Good quality and unique design. My baby won’t use them though.
